note right
Activity Description:

1. Admin accesses the Configure Rules page.
2. System fetches all available rule templates.
3. System displays current rule settings and status.
4. Admin selects which rules to enable or disable.
5. Admin sets severity levels for each rule.
6. Admin configures rule-specific thresholds.
7. Admin sets quality gates for PR approval.
8. System validates the entire configuration.
9. System checks if configuration is valid.
10. If invalid - displays validation errors.
11. If valid - admin reviews the rule summary.
12. Admin confirms approval of the configuration.
13. System saves rule configuration to database.
14. System updates the active rule set.
15. System displays success confirmation message.
16. If not approved - admin can modify rules.
end note

@enduml
